18/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The legislative commitments stemming from the Ohrid Peace Accord have been met completely, Local Self-Government Minister Aleksander Gestakovski told the daily <I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> on Saturday (16 August). He stressed that the provision for use of minority languages is in place in all municipalities, in the state administration and in the judicial and education sectors. Bilingual personal documents have become a fact of life, he added. Gestakovski said two important laws related to the Ohrid agreement have not yet been passed by parliament: the law on an ombudsman and the law on national symbols. (Utrinski Vesnik - 16/08/03)
